  "text": "Because in IR-UWB systems the duration of the pulses waveform is much less than bit duration T b , the integration time should be matched to these parts of UWB signal that contains considerable bit energy. This special property of UWB-IR systems has a serious effect on the noise performance, namely, it strongly depends on the product of B·T i . Then, the performance, which is a measure of E b /N 0 to achieve a certain bit-error-rate (BER), is strongly affected by the size of integration window time T i [CITATION_1] .",
